list_id.title: List ID
list_id.description: The list id for the growth activity report.

month.title: Month
month.description: The month that the growth history is describing.

subscribed.title: Subscribed
subscribed.description: Total subscribed members on the list at the end of the month.

unsubscribed.title: Unsubscribed
unsubscribed.description: Newly unsubscribed members on the list for a specific month.

reconfirm.title: Reconfirm
reconfirm.description: Newly reconfirmed members on the list for a specific month.

cleaned.title: Cleaned
cleaned.description: Newly cleaned (hard-bounced) members on the list for a specific month.

pending.title: Pending
pending.description: Pending members on the list for a specific month.

deleted.title: Deleted
deleted.description: Newly deleted members on the list for a specific month.

transactional.title: Transactional
transactional.description: Subscribers that have been sent transactional emails via Mandrill.

_links.title: Links
_links.description: A list of link types and descriptions for the API schema documents.

items.title: Resource Link
items.description: This object represents a link from the resource where it is found to another resource or action that may be performed.

rel.title: Rel
rel.description: As with an HTML 'rel' attribute, this describes the type of link.

href.title: Href
href.description: This property contains a fully-qualified URL that can be called to retrieve the linked resource or perform the linked action.

method.title: Method
method.description: The HTTP method that should be used when accessing the URL defined in 'href'.

targetSchema.title: Target Schema
targetSchema.description: For GETs, this is a URL representing the schema that the response should conform to.

schema.title: Schema
schema.description: For HTTP methods that can receive bodies (POST and PUT), this is a URL representing the schema that the body should conform to.
